CHAPTER XIII.

Hannibal entering Samnium lays waste the Reum-eman district, and takes Telesia. Endeavours to draw the Dictator into an engagement. Being induced by certain Campanians to try to get possession of Capua, orders a march to Casinum. The guide misunderstanding him, leads him to Casilinum. Guide seourged and crucified. The country between Falernum and Sinuessa ravaged. The Roman allies remain firm in their fidelity.-B.c. 217.
